# Supabase Edge Function secrets — COMMERCE (C-series).
#
# This is the contract only. Copy to `supabase/functions/.env` (git-ignored) and
# fill with TEST values first. NEVER commit real keys.
#
# Local function dev:
#   supabase functions serve --env-file supabase/functions/.env
# Push to the deployed project (prod runtime secrets):
#   supabase secrets set --env-file supabase/functions/.env --project-ref lgnmmcxvwdnusvfpguvf
#
# The frontend needs NO Stripe key: the checkout flow is a server-side redirect
# (the edge fn returns a hosted Checkout URL). A publishable key (pk_…) is only
# needed if we later switch to Stripe.js / embedded Checkout.

# Stripe restricted key. rk_test_… now; rk_live_… at go-live (L2).
# Mint in the Dashboard with LEAST-PRIVILEGE scopes (see STRIPE-HANDOFF.md C1):
#   Checkout Sessions: write · Prices: read · Products: read · Customers: write
#   Billing Portal Sessions: write · Subscriptions: read
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=

# Stripe webhook signing secret (whsec_…). Set in C3 when the webhook is registered.
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=

# Public site origin for Checkout success_url / cancel_url.
SITE_URL=https://orionfold.com

# --- Existing funnel secrets (already set in prod; here for local-dev parity) ---
# SUPABASE_URL=
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
# RESEND_API_KEY=
